The paper focuses on using deep learning techniques for emotion recognition in videos, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimodal learning (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of K-Means clustering (cs.SD) and relational autoencoders (cs.LG) for feature extraction and representation learning. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques for extracting features from the audio stream (cs.CL). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.MM, followed by cs.SD, cs.LG, and cs.CL.
